Me and @919999077274  have been recording class lectures for around 3 weeks now, as sharing every lecture on telegram been great, it comes with the problem of ' ease of access', as we have to deal with making large recording files into smaller ones. *If anyone has Problem with this method, they can post there issues in the Unofficial group or can contact me directly* 

The only thing needed here from all of you is commitment for the  betterment of mass.

I will start the process of migrating the content once everyone is onboard. Thankyou

09/09/21, 8:31 am - Anshul DTU: CLASS TEST 1- MSMA-101
1. Instructions to be followed during test:
• The duration for test is 1 hour.
• The exam is MCQ based and questions may have single correct or multiple correct answers.
Incase of multiple correct answers, marks will be awarded only when all the correct options
are marked.
• Google meet session will be recorded for future reference.
• Students have to keep their cameras switched on throughout the duration of the exam.
The camera should be placed at such an angle such that students upper body and hands
can be seen by the examiner.
• The student may keep blank sheets for calculations. All the sheets should be sequentially
numbered. The student should write his/her roll no, and name at the top of every sheet;
and put the signature at the bottom of every sheet. The student must keep these pages
for future reference, if needed.
• The video will be analyzed again by the department and in case, the student is found to
be indulged in using some unfair means, his/her paper will be cancelled.
• During the examination, gathering information from any kind of source or exchanging
information with others or any such attempt will be treated as ‘unfair means.’ Don’t
adopt unfair means and don’t indulge in unseemly behavior
• Once the test begins, the student is not allowed to change the tab/open a new tab on the
browser or access mobile or any other resourse.

04/10/21, 6:57 pm - Anshul DTU: *Abstract algebra*
1. Projects are to done in group of 2 only. Individual project is not allowed. 
2. Project should be well typed in Latex. 
3. There is no assignment of automorphism. But we need to prepare it's notes, which will be graded at the end of the semester under the class performance criteria, of 5 marks. 
4. The actual assignment will be uploaded on google classroom, most probably today itself, last date of submission will be monday. We can submit it either typed or hand written. 

Also, total 31 pairs are to be made for the project. So 31 topics will be there. Please select your partner and topic soon. I will make a form wherein everyone will fill their topics, so that no two pairs have the same topic.

19/10/21, 10:44 pm - Riya DTU: The Civil Services Examination (CSE) is a nationwide competitive examination in India conducted by the Union Public Service Commission for recruitment to higher Civil Services of the Government of India, including the Indian Administrative Service, Indian Foreign Service, and Indian Police Service. It is one of the most reputed examinations in India and require sheer hard work and dedication to get through. 
To answer all your doubts, the Training and Placement Department, DTU is organising a webinar in association with DTU(DCE) Alumni Association on the topic *"How To Prepare & Crack Civil Service Exams!"*. The students will get a golden opportunity to interact with the esteemed speakers and seek their guidance for the Civil Services Exams, from the strategies to prepare for the exam to the final interviews.

*Notable Mentions:*
*1. Prof. JP Saini*- Hon'ble Vice Chancellor, DTU & NSUT- Eminent academician, administrator and expert on important selection panels.

*2. Shree Karnal Singh (IPS)*- One of the most renowned IPS officers in the country, known for his commendable work during his tenure as Director, ED. Currently, he is actively involved in mentoring Civil Services aspirants.

*3. Ankita Jain* - Passed out of DTU in the year 2014, she secured an *All India Rank 3 in the UPSC exam.*

*4. Gaurav* - *All India Rank 13 in the UPSC exam.*

*5. Nisha* - Passed out of DTU in the year 2020, she secured an *All India Rank 117 in the UPSC exam*

*6. Shakti* - Qualified the IRS Examination in the year 2020 with flying colors.

*Date & Time: 23rd October 2021; 6:30 PM-8:30 PM*

Become a part of the session and get all your questions about the Civil Services exams answered.
To *register* and *listing your queries-* https://forms.gle/GvAK1pMEiyHk215R7
*Deadline to register: 6PM 21st October 2021*

20/10/21, 12:00 pm - Deepak Kumar: *As of now it can be seen that many of us wants to sit in placements, for the same when some of us visited DTU to meet Aditya sir i asked whether we are eligible to apply and he said as of now the placement cell don't recognise us as of worthy candidates. Our seniors and the batches before them faced similar issues with the placements. Sir told us that he raised this issue  last year but we weren't considered because of lack of hands on experience, for this Aditya sir said that in coming time a proper training schedule might get set up for placement of Masters students. The only thing it can take a lot of time without student support, the placement for the next year starts from May-December of the previous year. Its in all our hands to speed up the process and that is only possible if we show a strong support for the same.*

*As many of you haven't put up your names i just want to clarify that putting your name dosen't force you to ait on placements, just for your classmates you could all support the move, the more speedy the things would be the more advantage we could all get.*

*We are doing masters with so much of workloads (projects, assignments and whatnot), we don't deserve any less from BTech students. I hope more of you will support and we could all fight this issue together.*
